  "text": " Binders, glutathione, sauna, protocol dragging for months, nothing is clearing anymore. Client is doing everything by the book, binders, glutathione, sauna, maybe CSM. Some symptoms shift early than nothing. The protocol drags for months, sometimes years, nobody connects why. When I walk back through the sequence, one thing is almost always skipped, cell membrane repair. Here is the mechanism. Micotoxins are lipophilic. They store in cell membranes if the membrane is damaged from years of exposure, inflammation, oxidative stress. The binders never get a full release. The toxins keep recycling. The protocol keeps running, nothing moves. Fosphatidyl-coline is the phospholipid, the body uses to rebuild that membrane layer. Body bio PC is the form I reach for, usually introduced to four weeks before the binding protocol starts, or alongside it if the client can't wait. Micotoxins are lipophilic. They store in cell membranes. Binders without phospholipid support is why most protocols stall, not as a replacement for binders, as the floor of the binders are standing on. Full pattern breakdown at tr.e.e. slash awq7fm. Type it.",
